creator: False
bio:
Hello👋🏾 I am Ozzie, a tech girlie who brings a blend of technical and business skills to the table!

✨Skills highlight✨
React, Vue, JavaScript, TypeScript, Git, Node.js, Jest, Docker, Python, AWS, Agile

About me💻

During my bachelor's, I specialized in developing efficient and robust software solutions, after which I went into business in an EdTech startup. Afterwards, I pursued a master's in data science and joined a startup as a project manager.

It all sounds spread out but these experiences have contributed to me possessing the skills I have that make me quite the out-of-box software engineer. I hope to eventually contribute to a product that makes a practical change and fosters growth, learning, team spirit and creativity.



My areas of expertise include fullstack development and devops. I am open to new connections and opportunities.

name: David Orok
headline: Technology Entrepreneur | Founder of Nocode Africa | Product Marketer | Nocode App Developer
creator: True
school_2: Quantic School of Business and Technology
bio:
As a seasoned tech entrepreneur deeply passionate about technology and business, I’ve had the privilege to work in Project Management, Strategy, Marketing, and Product & Business Development—a combination that has given me a unique ability to solve problems creatively and help businesses scale.

In my role as a Product Marketing Strategist, I focus on:

✅Crafting compelling positioning and messaging that resonates with target audiences
✅Developing go-to-market strategies that drive product adoption and revenue growth
✅Collaborating cross-functionally to align product, marketing, and sales teams
✅Analyzing market trends and competitor insights to inform strategic decisions
✅Creating customer-centric content that drives engagement and showcases product value
✅Measuring and optimizing marketing performance through data-driven insights
✅Leading product launches to ensure seamless execution and maximum impact


As someone who thrives on innovation, I’ve dedicated my work to helping small and midsize businesses grow sustainably. I know firsthand the challenges that come with scaling, especially when resources are limited, and that’s why I’m committed to showing business owners how to leverage technology affordably.

One of my proudest achievements is founding Nocode Africa, an initiative focused on teaching early-stage African startup founders how to build mobile and web apps without the need to code. I believe that everyone should have access to the tools and knowledge required to turn ideas into reality—quickly and cost-effectively. I’ve helped over 100 startup founders build their MVPs and launch their businesses, guiding them through every step with mentorship, practical training, and a lot of heart.

Let's connect and grow together.
